    "descripcion_en": "More than an English academy, the Colombo Americano is one of the most constant cultural engines of Cali: a binational center where the exchange between Colombia and the United States becomes concerts, exhibitions, cinema and reading. At its headquarters in the traditional Granada neighborhood, the Humberto Hernández art gallery coexists—which showcases artists from both countries, always with free admission—, the Earle Sherman Auditorium, the Abraham Lincoln bilingual library with more than 4,000 titles, and the IdeaLab Makerspace, a 3D printing, robotics and digital creation laboratory. \n\nFounded in 1954 as a non-profit foundation, it has grown to have several branches in the southwest and more than five thousand students, but its heart remains cultural and, to a large extent, free. It is one of those places where the word “cultural” does not adorn the name: the programming is real, sustained and open doors.",
