    "descripcion_en": "Granada was born as a residential neighborhood at the beginning of the 20th century and over the years it became the most cosmopolitan face of Cali taste. Much of the city's haute cuisine is concentrated in its tree-lined streets: long-tablecloth restaurants, international proposals, specialty coffees and signature cocktails. It is the \"gourmet zone\" of Cali and a frequent starting point for gastronomic routes.\\n\\nBut not everything is a table: Lugar a Dudas, one of the most important contemporary art spaces in the city, operates in a house in the neighborhood. Thus, Granada mixes the pleasure of eating well with a cultural life that filters through restaurants and galleries.",
